---
layout: base
title: Reading calendar
description: A personal calendar of what you've read, drawn from this device's local reading history.
permalink: /reading-calendar/
---
<main class="container reading-cal" data-pagefind-ignore>

  <header class="reading-cal__header">
    <p class="reading-cal__kicker">Reader tools</p>
    <h1 class="reading-cal__title">Reading calendar</h1>
    <p class="reading-cal__lede">
      Your reading, day by day. Each cell shows how many articles you
      finished or substantially read on that date. Drawn entirely from
      this device&rsquo;s local history &mdash; no account, no server.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="reading-cal__summary" id="reading-cal-summary"></div>

  <div id="reading-cal-mount" class="reading-cal__mount" aria-live="polite">
    <p class="reading-cal__loading">Loading your reading history&hellip;</p>
  </div>

  <noscript>
    <p class="reading-cal__noscript">
      The reading calendar reads your local history with JavaScript.
      Without JS the calendar can&rsquo;t render.
    </p>
  </noscript>

</main>

<script src="/assets/js/reading-calendar.js?v={{ buildTime }}" defer></script>
